Citation.sTitle: Densities, Viscosities, and Speeds of Sound of the Nitromethane + 1-Pentanol System near the Critical Demixing Temperature: Effect of Deuterium Substitution
Citation.sAbstract: Densities, viscosities, and speeds of sound were measured for the binary mixtures of nitromethane and 1-pentanol and their deuterated forms in the vicinity of the upper critical solution temperature. The excess molar volumes and excess isentropic compressibilities as well as the deviations of viscosity were determined. The influence of the deuterium substitution was analyzed and discussed.
